<Link id="l00290" /><CodeLine lineNumber="290"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00291" /><CodeLine lineNumber="291"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//  Mips Asm Directives</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00292" /><CodeLine lineNumber="292"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00293" /><CodeLine lineNumber="293"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//  -- Frame directive &quot;frame Stackpointer, Stacksize, RARegister&quot;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00294" /><CodeLine lineNumber="294"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//  Describe the stack frame.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00295" /><CodeLine lineNumber="295"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00296" /><CodeLine lineNumber="296"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//  -- Mask directives &quot;(f)mask  bitmask, offset&quot;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00297" /><CodeLine lineNumber="297"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//  Tells the assembler which registers are saved and where.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00298" /><CodeLine lineNumber="298"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//  bitmask - contain a little endian bitset indicating which registers are</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00299" /><CodeLine lineNumber="299"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//            saved on function prologue (e.g. with a 2147483648 mask, the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00300" /><CodeLine lineNumber="300"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//            assembler knows the register 31 (RA) is saved at prologue.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00301" /><CodeLine lineNumber="301"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//  offset  - the position before stack pointer subtraction indicating where</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00302" /><CodeLine lineNumber="302"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//            the first saved register on prologue is located. (e.g. with a</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00303" /><CodeLine lineNumber="303"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00304" /><CodeLine lineNumber="304"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//  Consider the following function prologue:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00305" /><CodeLine lineNumber="305"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00306" /><CodeLine lineNumber="306"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//    .frame  $fp,48,$ra</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00307" /><CodeLine lineNumber="307"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//    .mask   0xc0000000,-8</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00308" /><CodeLine lineNumber="308"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//       addiu $sp, $sp, -48</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00309" /><CodeLine lineNumber="309"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//       sw $ra, 40($sp)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00310" /><CodeLine lineNumber="310"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//       sw $fp, 36($sp)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00311" /><CodeLine lineNumber="311"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00312" /><CodeLine lineNumber="312"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//    With a 3221225472 mask, the assembler knows the register 31 (RA) and</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00313" /><CodeLine lineNumber="313"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//    30 (FP) are saved at prologue. As the save order on prologue is from</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00314" /><CodeLine lineNumber="314"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//    left to right, RA is saved first. A -8 offset means that after the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00315" /><CodeLine lineNumber="315"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//    stack pointer subtration, the first register in the mask (RA) will be</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00316" /><CodeLine lineNumber="316"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//    saved at address 48-8=40.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00317" /><CodeLine lineNumber="317"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00318" /><CodeLine lineNumber="318"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00319" /><CodeLine lineNumber="319"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00320" /><CodeLine lineNumber="320"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00321" /><CodeLine lineNumber="321"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Mask directives</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00322" /><CodeLine lineNumber="322"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l01107" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1107"><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">void</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> MipsAsmPrinter::EmitSled(</span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">const</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/machineinstr">MachineInstr</a> &amp;<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/codegen/lib/codegen/globalisel/irtranslator-cpp/#abe44dfdea65b4f7e11e0a608ab708b76">MI</a>, SledKind Kind) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01108" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1108"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">const</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> uint8&#95;t NoopsInSledCount = <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/mipsasmprinter/#a757b743b9e44d55d713f89431155835c">Subtarget</a>-&gt;<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/mipssubtarget/#a9b50ba1092e9b3e6d57c4170d739133e">isGP64bit</a>() ? 15 : 11;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01109" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1109"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// For mips32 we want to emit the following pattern:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01110" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1110"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01111" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1111"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// .Lxray&#95;sled&#95;N:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01112" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1112"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   ALIGN</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01113" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1113"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   B .tmpN</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01114" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1114"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   11 NOP instructions (44 bytes)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01115" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1115"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   ADDIU T9, T9, 52</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01116" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1116"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// .tmpN</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01117" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1117"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01118" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1118"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// We need the 44 bytes (11 instructions) because at runtime, we&#39;d</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01119" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1119"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// be patching over the full 48 bytes (12 instructions) with the following</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01120" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1120"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// pattern:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01121" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1121"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01122" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1122"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   ADDIU    SP, SP, -8</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01123" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1123"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   NOP</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01124" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1124"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   SW       RA, 4(SP)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01125" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1125"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   SW       T9, 0(SP)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01126" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1126"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   LUI      T9, %hi(&#95;&#95;xray&#95;FunctionEntry/Exit)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01127" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1127"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   ORI      T9, T9, %lo(&#95;&#95;xray&#95;FunctionEntry/Exit)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01128" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1128"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   LUI      T0, %hi(function&#95;id)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01129" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1129"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   JALR     T9</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01130" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1130"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   ORI      T0, T0, %lo(function&#95;id)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01131" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1131"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   LW       T9, 0(SP)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01132" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1132"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   LW       RA, 4(SP)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01133" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1133"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   ADDIU    SP, SP, 8</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01134" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1134"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01135" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1135"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// We add 52 bytes to t9 because we want to adjust the function pointer to</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01136" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1136"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// the actual start of function i.e. the address just after the noop sled.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01137" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1137"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// We do this because gp displacement relocation is emitted at the start of</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01138" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1138"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// of the function i.e after the nop sled and to correctly calculate the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01139" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1139"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// global offset table address, t9 must hold the address of the instruction</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01140" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1140"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// containing the gp displacement relocation.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01141" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1141"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// FIXME: Is this correct for the static relocation model?</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01142" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1142"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01143" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1143"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// For mips64 we want to emit the following pattern:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01144" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1144"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01145" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1145"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// .Lxray&#95;sled&#95;N:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01146" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1146"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   ALIGN</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01147" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1147"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   B .tmpN</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01148" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1148"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   15 NOP instructions (60 bytes)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01149" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1149"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// .tmpN</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01150" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1150"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01151" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1151"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// We need the 60 bytes (15 instructions) because at runtime, we&#39;d</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l01153" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1153"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// pattern:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01154" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1154"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01155" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1155"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   DADDIU   SP, SP, -16</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01156" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1156"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   NOP</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01157" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1157"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   SD       RA, 8(SP)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01158" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1158"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   SD       T9, 0(SP)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01159" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1159"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   LUI      T9, %highest(&#95;&#95;xray&#95;FunctionEntry/Exit)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01160" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1160"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   ORI      T9, T9, %higher(&#95;&#95;xray&#95;FunctionEntry/Exit)</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l01162" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1162"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   ORI      T9, T9, %hi(&#95;&#95;xray&#95;FunctionEntry/Exit)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01163" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1163"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   DSLL     T9, T9, 16</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01164" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1164"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   ORI      T9, T9, %lo(&#95;&#95;xray&#95;FunctionEntry/Exit)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01165" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1165"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   LUI      T0, %hi(function&#95;id)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01166" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1166"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   JALR     T9</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01167" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1167"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   ADDIU    T0, T0, %lo(function&#95;id)</span></CodeLine>
